 "But when I saw these old sorts my spittle ran, and I was desirous to eat thereof as though I were a child. I rent the paper packaging of the first biscuit and devoured with winne,"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a mark that is fired at (such as a bullseye), a target", "tags": ["countable", "obsolete"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Etymology tree\nAncient Greek χάρτης (khártēs)bor.\nAramaic קַרְטִיסָא /ܩܲܪܛܝܼܣܵܐ (qarṭīsā)bor.\nArabic قرطاس\nFrom Aramaic קַרְטִיסָא / ܩܲܪܛܝܼܣܵܐ (qarṭīsā), from Ancient Greek χάρτης (khártēs)."}, "ipa": ["/qir.tˤaːs/", "/qur.tˤaːs/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n35533", "headword_ar": "قِرْطَاسٌ", "root": "qrTs", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Paper;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAgadN", "text_ar": "كَاغَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as is made of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "barodiY~", "text_ar": "بَرْدِىّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "papyrus"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "found in Egypt:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) [and particularly"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a roll,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "scroll, thereof:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TuwmaArN", "text_ar": "طُومَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "surofapN", "text_ar": "سُرْفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what one writes upon:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb:) also written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "quroTaAsN", "text_ar": "قُرْطَاسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, Msb, K;) but the former is the better known, (Msb), or the former only is of established authority, for El-Járabardee says the contrary of the latter; (MF;) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qar